Vedh — Project Architecture & Directory Details

This document outlines the folder structure, module purposes, and developer notes for Vedh.

========================================================================
📂 DIRECTORY STRUCTURE & MODULE DETAILS
========================================================================

vedh/
│
├── .github/
│   └── workflows/
│       └── release.yml        ← CI/CD pipeline: Automates PyInstaller compiles and GitHub Releases on tags (v*)
│
├── app/
│   └── main.py                ← Main application entrypoint. Initializes database, loads fonts, themes, and views
│
├── assets/                    ← Static files bundled with the application
│   ├── fonts/                 ← Application fonts (Lora-Regular, Lora-Italic, motterdam, etc.)
│   └── images/                ← UI icons, application logo, and the lotus window icon (lotus.ico)
│
├── core/                      ← Core non-UI business logic and managers
│   ├── book_model.py          ← BookMetadata definitions and structural parser logic
│   ├── config_manager.py      ← Reads/writes global configuration values (JSON)
│   ├── plugin_manager.py      ← Registers and executes modular reader plugins
│   ├── theme_manager.py       ← Loads and compiles active stylesheet rules (app and reader)
│   └── updater.py             ← GitHub Release checker, thread-safe downloader, and SHA-256 hash verifier
│
├── engines/                   ← Content extraction engines for document formats
│   ├── comic_engine.py        ← Handler for CBR/CBZ graphic novels and image sets
│   ├── epub_engine.py         ← EPUB parser, resource extractor, and stylesheet processor
│   └── pdf_engine.py          ← PDF document render pipeline
│
├── rendering/                 ← Flow layout engine and UI rendering routines
│   ├── image_renderer.py      ← Renders and scales images/covers to preserve page constraints
│   ├── layout.py              ← Manages margin calculations and text blocks
│   ├── text_renderer.py       ← Renders and justifies multi-font text layout
│   └── pagination/            ← Page distribution calculators
│       ├── cache.py           ← Stores pre-paginated index bounds for instantaneous page turning
│       ├── engine.py          ← Combines measurers and caches to paginate e-books
│       └── measurer.py        ← Measures string size bounds on a graphics canvas
│
├── storage/                   ← Data persistence layers
│   ├── database.py            ← Initializes SQLite DB schemas (~/.vedh/vedh.db)
│   └── repositories.py        ← Repository classes for Books and Art creations
│
├── themes/                    ← Style definitions
│   ├── app/                   ← UI theme layouts (dark.json, light.json)
│   └── reader/                ← Reader canvas palettes (default.json, night.json, sepia.json)
│
├── ui/                        ← PyQt6 UI views and widget components
│   ├── widgets/               ← Reusable UI elements (toast.py, custom overlays)
│   ├── art_view.py            ← 3D book-like artwork gallery and flip controls
│   ├── book_card.py           ← Grid cards representing books in the library
│   ├── convert_dialog.py      ← E-book conversion loading window
│   ├── home_view.py           ← Dashboard showing reading statistics and book shortcuts
│   ├── library_view.py        ← Book library grid, search, and import controls
│   ├── main_window.py         ← Sidebar navigation shell and startup update check
│   ├── metadata_dialog.py     ← Dialog to edit book details and fetch covers
│   ├── reader_view.py         ← E-book reader canvas with dual-page book rendering
│   ├── settings_view.py       ← Settings panel (themes, fonts, reset, update checking)
│   ├── sidebar.py             ← Sidebar navigation controller
│   └── toc_panel.py           ← Interactive Table of Contents sidebar for books
│
├── installer/                 ← Deployment resources
│   ├── Product.wxs            ← WiX Toolset installer definition file
│   └── License.rtf            ← End User License Agreement (EULA) screen RTF file
│
├── venv/                      ← Local python virtual environment (excluded from git)
│
├── dist/                      ← Output directory for PyInstaller and WiX compilations (excluded from git)
├── build/                     ← PyInstaller intermediate build cache (excluded from git)
│
├── updater.py                 ← Standalone python script compiled to updater.exe (clean-swaps binaries)
├── Vedh.spec                  ← PyInstaller spec configuration file
└── .gitignore                 ← Git exclusion rules (ignores cache, build, logs, database)

