========================================================================
🚀 AUTORELEASE & UPDATE SYSTEM
========================================================================

* GitHub Actions Workflow:
  Compiles "updater.py" (console, onefile) and "app/main.py" (windowed, paths=".") into the dist/ directory.
  Injects "updater.exe" into the application's root directory, zips it, calculates the SHA-256 hash, and drafts a release.

* Self- Updater Client:
  On launch, "main_window.py" runs an async check. If a release tag higher than v0.1.0 is found, it shows a toast message.
  In settings, clicking "Check for Updates" displays a modal dialog, downloads the update file, verifies the hash, extracts the ZIP, launches "updater.exe", and exits.
  "updater.exe" waits for the main app to close, wipes all old files (preserving ~/.vedh/ data), copies the new version files, and launches the updated Vedh.exe.


